    "source": "Census 2011 sub-district directory; state revenue department websites for naming cross-check.",
    "caveat": "Block-level population from Census 2011 PDF tables is not yet integrated — V2 lists block names + parent district only. Each block is headed by a Tahsildar / Block Development Officer (BDO), typically state civil service, not IAS. The state-cadre IAS list rarely extends below district headquarters. Naming uses Census 2011 sub-district directory transliterations; minor variations vs current state-revenue-dept usage may exist (e.g., 'Tehsil' vs 'Tahsil').",
